  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Response to the Floods in Bamako</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">On 28 August 2013, heavy rains hit Bamako, causing the river to rapidly and significantly overflow, in turn causing severe flooding in two of the six communes of the district. The floods have caused the death of 34 people (as of 30 August 2013)  - but this figure could increase as some people are still reported missing. In addition, 1,539 families were displaced. Some of these displaced families have been referred to five emergency reception centres. Oxfam provided NFI kits (assistance to 1,500 persons) to contribute to the government efforts.</narrative>
  </description>
